# Technical Architecture

## Overview

The Survonomics ecosystem is designed as a secure, scalable, and modular platform that supports millions of users while maintaining high performance, strong security, and seamless integration across all products.

The architecture follows a shared-core approach, where common services power multiple applications, reducing duplication and improving maintainability.

---

# Ecosystem Architecture

The Survonomics ecosystem consists of four integrated applications:

- SurvMessenger
- SurvPay
- SurvPrice
- SurvMarket

Each application serves a distinct purpose while sharing authentication, security, notifications, storage, and infrastructure.

---

# Technology Stack

## Mobile

- Flutter

Supports Android and iOS from a single codebase.

---

## Backend

- Node.js
- Express.js

Provides REST APIs, real-time communication, authentication, and business logic.

---

## Database

- PostgreSQL

Stores user accounts, projects, transactions, marketplace data, pricing information, and application settings.

---

## Cache

- Redis

Used for:

- Session management
- Caching
- Rate limiting
- Performance optimization
- Temporary data

---

## File Storage

Secure cloud object storage is used for:

- Documents
- Drawings
- Images
- Videos
- Project files

---

## Real-Time Communication

Real-time infrastructure powers:

- Messaging
- Notifications
- Typing indicators
- Presence status
- Voice signalling
- Video signalling

---

# Security Architecture

Security is implemented using a defense-in-depth approach.

## Authentication

- Email authentication
- Phone authentication
- Multi-factor authentication
- JWT access tokens
- Refresh tokens

---

## Authorization

Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

Examples:

- Client
- Contractor
- Architect
- Quantity Surveyor
- Supplier
- Project Manager
- Administrator

Each role receives only the permissions required.

---

## Encryption

- HTTPS/TLS
- Encrypted database storage
- End-to-end encrypted messaging
- Secure password hashing
- Secure API communication

---

## API Protection

- Rate limiting
- Request validation
- Token verification
- Audit logging
- Activity monitoring

---

# Shared Core Services

Every application uses common services including:

- Authentication
- Notifications
- File storage
- User profiles
- Professional verification
- Search
- Logging
- Analytics

This reduces duplication across the ecosystem.

---

# AI Integration

Artificial Intelligence will support:

- Construction assistance
- Document summarization
- Cost estimation
- Project insights
- Procurement recommendations
- Smart search
- Workflow automation

AI operates within permission boundaries to protect user privacy.

---

# Scalability

The platform is designed for horizontal scaling.

Future capabilities include:

- Load balancing
- Containerization
- Auto scaling
- Distributed services
- Multiple database replicas
- Global CDN
- Multi-region deployment

---

# Monitoring

System health is monitored continuously through:

- Error logging
- Performance metrics
- Infrastructure monitoring
- Security alerts
- Backup monitoring
- Audit trails

---

# Disaster Recovery

The platform includes:

- Automated backups
- Database replication
- Recovery procedures
- High availability
- Business continuity planning

---

# Future Architecture

As Survonomics grows, the platform will evolve into a distributed architecture capable of supporting millions of users while maintaining security, reliability, and performance.

---

# Engineering Principles

Every technical decision follows these principles:

- Security by Design
- Simplicity
- Scalability
- Reliability
- Maintainability
- Performance
- Privacy First
- Modular Development
- Continuous Improvement

---

# Vision

The Survonomics technical architecture is designed not only to support today's needs but to serve as the long-term digital infrastructure powering the construction industry across Africa and, ultimately, the global market.
